phases.task:
You are the final arbiter reviewing the current working tree against OpenSpec change `{args.change}`. Consolidate the evidence below into ONE report.

Reviewer findings are CLAIMS, not facts. You have read/grep/ls: before confirming any [blocker] or [major] finding, VERIFY it against the actual code — open the file, check the lines, confirm the problem reproduces in source. Reject findings that do not hold up, however confident they sound.

Build/test output (ends with VERIFY_EXIT=<code>; non-zero means tests failed):
{steps.build-test.output}

Spec validation (ends with VALIDATE_EXIT=<code>):
{steps.spec-validate.output}

Diff:
{steps.diff.output}

Spec-compliance review (Claude):
{steps.review-spec-claude.output}

Spec-compliance review (Kimi):
{steps.review-spec-kimi.output}

Correctness review (Claude, recall-tuned):
{steps.review-bugs-claude.output}

Correctness review (GPT, precision-tuned):
{steps.review-bugs-gpt.output}

Simplicity review (GPT):
{steps.review-kiss-gpt.output}

Simplicity review (GLM):
{steps.review-kiss-glm.output}

Security review (Claude, recall-tuned):
{steps.review-sec-claude.output}

Security review (GPT, precision-tuned):
{steps.review-sec-gpt.output}

Rules:
- An empty review section means that reviewer was skipped — note it, do not treat silence as approval.
- Mechanical snippet check: every finding must quote verbatim code from the cited file. Grep the quote in that file (whitespace-insensitive); no match = REJECT the finding outright.
- Coverage audit: cross-check each reviewer's `Coverage:` section against the FILES CHANGED manifest in the diff. A file skipped or unmentioned by ALL reviewers of an angle is an uncovered gap — list it in the report; never treat silence as reviewed.
- Where the two reviewers of one angle disagree, adjudicate explicitly against the code and say which one you believe and why.
- VERIFY_EXIT or VALIDATE_EXIT non-zero MUST result in BLOCK. Also block on any verified [blocker] finding, on unimplemented requirements, or on tests weakened to pass. Use judgment on [major]/[minor] — cite why you accept or reject each.

Structure: verdict first, then confirmed findings (with file:line, each marked VERIFIED after your own code check), then rejected findings with one-line reasons, then skipped reviewers. End with exactly `VERDICT: PASS`, or `VERDICT: BLOCK` followed by a precise numbered fix list. If uncertain, BLOCK.

Write the final review report for `{args.change}` for a human. WRITE THE REPORT IN CZECH (čeština) — it is the only output the human reads. Keep file paths, code identifiers, command names, and the `VERDICT:` line in English.

Arbiter verdict:
{steps.verdict.output}

Fix stage output:
{steps.fix.output}

Re-check after fixes (VERIFY_EXIT=0 means tests pass):
{steps.recheck.output}

Confirm gate (verified the fixes against the code; empty means it was skipped or still blocking after retries — treat that as NEEDS ATTENTION):
{steps.confirm.output}

Structure: overall outcome first (clean pass / fixed & verified / needs attention), confirmed findings, fixes applied + tests added (or none), disputed findings, skipped reviewers. If fixes were applied, recommend re-running `/tf:openspec-review change={args.change}` for a fresh panel pass. Close with the next steps: `/plannotator-review`, then `openspec archive {args.change}`.
